         <change when="2026-04-23T03:33:59-04:00"
                 who="http://papyri.info/editor/users/j.lougovaya.ast">Vote - Return-Straight-to-Sender - This needs correcting because of Bernand's unconventional use of parentheses. What he prints as προσκύνη(μα) in line one means that μα is a supralinear insertion, so please encode accordingly. In line 3, χαλ(κε)ύς means that he sees a ligatured κε. Neither Lepsius nor Reinach saw the epislon (nor do I). I suggest encoding χαλκύς in the text and regularizing it to χαλκεύς.</change>
